data.name: label1.Text
data.value: Most coordinate formats are accepted in these windows. The program will interpret your string and convert to the appropriate format displayed in the text box label. Textboxes allow quick copying by double-click. Quadrants (N, S, E, W) may lead or follow the coordinates. Errors are always displayed as "199.00.00" Bounds (+/- 90 Lat, +/- 180 Lon) are enforced. Acceptable formats: - VRC: [D]DD.MM.SS.sss - Decimal Degrees: [D]DD.ddddddd (S && W are neg) - FAA data file: [D]DD-MM-SS.ssss - FAA Seconds: SSSSS.sssss - NaviGraph: {D]DD MM.sssssss - Rich Text DD°MM'SS[.ss]"
